From cou.: 25 We propose in the following a microscopic model for the yielding or gelation, corresponding to ā approaching 0 or 1 respectively, of a physical gel using an essentially bi-parametric family of a correlated site percolation model37 that extends the uncorrelated version26 towards a correlated version33 but with an emphasis on the effects of externally applied and time-varying stress ramps. Our model builds on the analogy between the local agglomerative interactions in terms of assembly/disassembly of neighbouring gel particles in a microscopic gel network—see ref. 31 (2.5,2.6,5.9,5.9.1,5.9.1.1,8.1.4) and ref. 32 for standardized nomenclature—subjected to an external stress field.
From Soup: 25 We propose in the following a microscopic model for the yielding or gelation, corresponding to ā approaching 0 or 1 respectively, of a physical gel using an essentially bi-parametric family of a correlated site percolation model 37 that extends the uncorrelated version 26 towards a correlated version 33 but with an emphasis on the effects of externally applied and time-varying stress ramps. Our model builds on the analogy between the local agglomerative interactions in terms of assembly/disassembly of neighbouring gel particles in a microscopic gel network—see ref. 31 (2.5,2.6,5.9,5.9.1,5.9.1.1,8.1.4) and ref. 32 for standardized nomenclature—subjected to an external stress field.
