From cou.: 232 Let the initial site configuration be all fluid with x(0) = 0 and (ā(x(0)),(x(0))) = (0,0). We model aging by the time evolution of the site configuration, i.e. by x(m) as m → ∞, or equivalently in rescaled time by x(t) as t → ∞, where m = [tn2]. The material as it ages may or may not form a gel depending on the parameters α and β. For various values of α and β we obtain insights from Monte Carlo simulations of stress-free gelation, i.e., for the fluid–solid (F–S) phase transition to occur in the absence of external stress.
