From cou.: 310 B.4 Ising model.
From cou.: 311 Our model can be reparametrized as the Ising model29,30 with phases given by {−1,+1} for the ferromagnetic spins due to the well-known transformation (for e.g. see Problem 3, Chapter 138). Despite this mathematical equivalence, one looses interpretability of yielded and unyielded states of the microscopic clumps readily available in the correlated site percolation with phases in {0,1}.
